	<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Part_collection_mim
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:mim:Part_collection_mim"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_mim"/>
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_mim.schema_name">
A <b>schema_name</b> is a constant that specifies an uppercase representation of the name of the present Express schema.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_mim  Rule: restrict_collection_category 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:mim:Part_collection_mim.restrict_collection_category"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_mim.restrict_collection_category">
The <b>restrict_collection_category</b> rule constrains every instance of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> of type 'collection definition' to be a definition of a <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product"/> of category 'collection'.
</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_mim.restrict_collection_category.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product"/> referenced by the  attribute "of product" of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_formation"/> that is not a 'collection'.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Part_collection_mim  Rule: restrictproduct_definition_for_collection 
   <express_ref linkend="part_collection:mim:Part_collection_mim.restrict_product_definition_for_collection"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_collection">
The <b>restrict_product_definitions_for_collection</b> rule restricts the name of instances of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> when they are related by a <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/>  with name 'collection membership'.
<p>The name of the relating <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> shall be 'part definition'.
In addition, this  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> shall have an associated definition context with name 'collection definition'.
</p>
		<p>The name of the related <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/>  shall be 'part occurrence'.
</p>
	</ext_description>
	<ext_description linkend="Part_collection_mim.restrict_product_definitions_for_collection.wr:WR1">
There shall not be any instance of  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition_relationship"/> with name 'collection membership', for which the name of the related instances of <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> does not match the constraint mentioned above.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
